cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY

This paper deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Graph Theory to cluster news articles based on their content. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses tools from Graph Theory, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) possible sub-categories. The paper also deals with information retrieval and classification, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses deep neural networks, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
